PLACEHOLDER — replace with the real file `avatar_reference.png` in this folder.

What it is
  The canonical identity image of YOUR synthetic avatar, used by the DINOv2
  identity gate (FR-6). Every sampled frame of every generated video is
  compared against this image; anything scoring below identity.cosine_min
  (config.yaml) is retried and then flagged — never published.

Requirements
  - A clean, front-facing, well-lit render of the avatar (head + upper body),
    ideally one of the images the character LoRA was trained on.
  - PNG, roughly 768–1024 px on the short side.
  - Same file the LoRA identity derives from — if you retrain the avatar,
    update this image too.

How to install it
  1. Save the image as:  assets/avatar_reference.png
  2. Delete this placeholder file.
  3. `paths.avatar_reference` in config.yaml already points there.

Until the real file exists, worker.py fails the identity-gate stage with a
clear setup error (the URL is not consumed).
